definitions.definition: ( Roman mythology ) The daughter of Latona and Jupiter , and twin sister of Apollo ; the goddess of the hunt, associated wild animals and the forest or wilderness, and an emblem of chastity ; the Roman counterpart of Artemis .
( astronomy ) 78 Diana , a main belt asteroid .
( astronomy , mythology ) The Moon ; the Moon as a deity.
A female given name from Latin .
